Label: The unique identifier representing each tile. Useful for spatial indexing, partitioning, and storing and deriving the tile geometry.
The code representing a specific country. The National boundary.
The name representing a specific country in Spanish. The National boundary.
The code representing a subdivision of a country, such as a state or province. First-level administrative divisions.
The name representing a subdivision of a country in Spanish. First-level administrative divisions.
The code representing a further subdivision, such as a municipality. Second-level administrative divisions
The name representing a further subdivision in Spanish. Second-level administrative divisions
Trimester of the year for the data
The average download speed of all tests performed in the tile, measured in kilobits per second.
The average upload speed of all tests performed in the tile, measured in kilobits per second.
The average latency of all tests performed in the tile, measured in milliseconds.
The total number of tests taken in the tile.
The total number of unique devices contributing tests in the tile.
